Tkinter is a standard GUI (Graphical User Interface) library in Python used to create desktop applications.

ðŸ”¹ What is Tkinter?
Tkinter allows you to create windows, buttons, text boxes, labels, menus, and other GUI elements for desktop software using Python.
It comes pre-installed with Python, so no extra installation is needed.

ðŸ”¹ Features of Tkinter
Easy to use and beginner-friendly
Built-in with Python
Used to create desktop applications

Supports widgets like:
1) Button
2) Label
3) Text box
4) Entry field
5) Checkbox
6) Radio button
7) Menu

ðŸ”¹ Basic Structure of Tkinter Program

Import tkinter
Create main window
Add widgets (button, label, etc.)
Run the application
